Meet Our Team | Triad Hybrid Solutions | Triad Advisors



















Show Nav




Triad Advisors
Meet Our Team






Michael C. Bryan
Chief Executive Officer

Michael C. Bryan is Chief Executive Officer at Triad Hybrid Solutions. Michael is responsible for the firm’s vision, model and strategic development. He also offers consultation and education regarding the growth of advisors’ individual practices and the advancement of industry partnerships. Michael began in the fee-based advisor world over 15 years ago and also acts as Senior Vice President at Triad Advisors, Inc. where he has managed the Advisory Services platform since 2005. He is responsible for the team that provides the firm’s account structures, products, services and strategic partnerships, which allow advisors to offer fee-based solutions to clients. Like the approach at Triad Hybrid Solutions, his team also acts as consultant to advisors in converting to and growing the fee-based portion of their independent practice. Michael continues to live where he grew up, in Atlanta, where he is active in his community and various organizations, as well as proudly serving as a member of FSI’s Investment Advisory Council for whom he has served as past Chair.

Show More







Amy Rehn, MSOL
Chief Operating Officer

Amy Rehn, MSOL, is Chief Operating Officer at Triad Hybrid Solutions. Amy is responsible for the execution of the firm’s mandate to deliver expert and pleasant consultation, service and back office support. She is also responsible for the evaluation and advisor awareness of strategic partnerships. Amy began her career in Financial Services in 2001 and currently serves as Senior Vice President in Advisory Services for Triad Advisors, Inc. In that role she develops and executes advisor education efforts and offers direct advisor consultation. She manages the more complex advisory systems, working to ensure proper functionality and issue resolution. Amy is the editor of the firm’s quarterly magazine, The Triad Times, and writes the advisor spotlight feature in each issue. Mrs. Rehn is also a committee member of the Ladenburg Institute of Women and Finance. She holds her Series 7 and 66 licenses. Amy is a Georgia native living in the Atlanta area with her husband and two children.

Show More







David Belotte, CFA
Chief Compliance Officer

David Belotte, CFA is Chief Compliance Officer at Triad Hybrid Solutions, ensuring the RIA and all affiliated IARs are compliant with industry rules and regulations. David joined Triad in 2010 and also serves as Deputy CCO and VP of affiliated RIA Triad Advisors, Inc. He has a BBA in Finance and Economics from Baruch College and holds his Series 3, 4, 7, 24 and 63 licenses. He has held various roles at Smith Barney, Prudential and Etrade. David is originally from New York City and currently resides in the Atlanta area with his wife and son.

Show More






